Package: ppmData
Type: Package
Title: Quasi-random Quadrature Scheme using Dirichlet Tessellation for Spatial Poisson Point Process Models
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Skipton", "Woolley", email = "skip.woolley@csiro.au", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Scott", "Foster", email = "scott.foster@data61.csiro.au", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Skipton Woolley <skip.woolley@csiro.au>
Description: Quasi-random sampling to generate a quadrature scheme for Poisson point process models. Quadrature weights are calculate for point using Dirichlet tessellation. The resulting object can be used in existing single and multiple species models in order to extend them to Point Processes.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
